  <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
    <h3>How to bring it within budget</h3>
    <p>The gap between the mid-range and your $300,000–350,000 target is closed primarily through three levers. First, site selection — a gentle, accessible parcel with good road frontage saves $20,000–40,000 in driveway and site work alone compared to a steep remote lot. Second, owner-builder participation in the hempcrete laying phase — this is genuinely learnable and directly reduces the largest labor line item. Third, phasing the cob details, screened porch, and stone patio into year two rather than building everything at once. The house is livable before those elements are complete. The land is patient.</p>
